CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 24, 1954, pg. 11, reads: "Alpha Picnic - As usual the Alpha picnic attracted a large crowd of fun-lovers who responded to the clever invitations sent out by the members of the fraternity, by taking them up on their invite to spend a day with Robin Hood in Sherwood's Forest. In photos on the left and right are members of the committee, dressed in authentic costumes of Robin Hood's era. In the first photo: Charles Angell and Howard [Hairston] are surrounded by William Dorsey, Dr. Robert C. Bolden, Charles Cuthbert, John Cundieff, and Forrest (Bud) Parr... - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Alpha Phi Alpha Fraternity members Charles Angell, Howard Hairston, William Dorsey, Dr. Robert C. Bolden, Charles Cuthbert, John Cundieff, and Forrest (Bud) Parr wearing Robin Hood style costumes at Alpha picnic, North Park
